BRIEFING: DEPT GATE: E11 / ARR GATE: NOT ASSIGNED (GATE(S) ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE) PAX COUNTS: F 15 / Y 185 / NR 10 (PAX COUNTS ARE PRELIMINARY)
ADDTN'L FUEL FOR LONG TAXI TIMES
BOS: VFR, WINDS BECOMING LIGHT TO CALMINCREASING SW WINDS TUE WITH GUSTS TO 20-25 KT DEVELOPING IN THE AFTERNOON.
CONUS: A LOW LVL JTST AT FL320 GOATR AND AHPAH. FAVORABLE CONDITIONS CROSSING THE GREAT LAKES THRU THE MIDWEST. A LOW-PRESSURE SYS SITS IN THE NE CORNER OF SOUTH DAKOTA. POSSIBLE TURB CROSSING THE AREA AND CONTINUING OVER THE ROCKIES. CLEAR CONDITIONS FROM OVER NEVADA AND CALIFORNIA.
ETOPS/TRACKS: HIGH LVL MOD TURB POSSIBLE CROSSING THE CALIFORNIA COASTLINE THRU THE FIR BOUNDARY UP FL400. CLD COVERAGE BTWN BARAZ THRU BILLO. POSSIBLE TURB THRU THESE POINTS ASSOCIATED WITH A JTST AT FL400.
HAWAII TERMINALS: MODERATE TO BREEZY EASTERLY TRADES WILL CONTINUE THROUGH MONDAY. PASSING CLOUDS AND BRIEF SHOWERS WILL FAVOR WINDWARD AND MOUNTAIN SLOPES DURING THE OVERNIGHT TO EARLY MORNING HOURS.
AIRMET TANGO FOR LOW-LEVEL TURBULENCE DOWNSTREAM OF ISLAND TERRAIN IS LIKELY BY MONDAY AFTERNOON DUE TO THE STRENGTHENING TRADE WINDS.
THREAT: SPACE WEATHER: NONE
NOTAMS PLEASE REVIEW NOTAMS SECTION OF PACKET FOR MOST CURRENT INFORMATION
